news.title: China's Kaisa Group aims to present offshore debt revamp plan in Q4 2022: Sources
news.para: Kaisa is working to restructure its offshore debt after missing some debt obligations last year. With $12 billion of offshore debt, it is China's largest issuer of offshore debt among developers after China Evergrande Group.

news.title: Chennai: Water meters planned in every household in five years
news.para: In the first phase, meters will be fixed in 50,000 commercial establishments, multi-storey buildings, apartment complexes and partly commercial establishments by March 2023. An assessment will be done and a metering policy framed.

news.title: Delhi HC asks Ansals to reply to victims' plea on enhancing punishment in Uphaar case
news.para: ​Justice Asha Menon issued notice to the Ansal brothers and the state on the petition by Association of Victims of Uphaar Tragedy (AVUT) and asked them to file their response while listing the matter for further hearing on October 11.

news.title: Odisha government notifies Rs 270 crore rainwater harvesting scheme
news.para: Any person owning a building having a roof area less than 200 square metres and not more than three floors in the specified civic bodies will be eligible to apply under the scheme, the guidelines said.

news.title: Delhi: Covid, construction ban delay Nehru Palace's redevelopment
news.para: While the overall upgrade work was started by DDA in December 2019 after getting a no-objection certificate from the South Delhi Municipal Corporation, the skywalk started taking shape only earlier this year.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh government to take houses on rent for employees
news.para: Models like hire purchase model and annuity model would be considered by the government. A committee has been constituted to finalize details in a month. As a pilot, it would be first started in major cities of the state.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government allots new homes for 120 residents of demolished housing unit
news.para: Muthusamy said the 1,072 tenements that were built in 1983 for the slum dwellers at Karungalpalayam were demolished, as they were in dilapidated condition and uninhabitable.

news.title: Goa's IT department takes step towards drawing up policy for co-working spaces
news.para: Khaunte said that DoIT has already identified land at Morjim, Caranzalem and Benaulim where the three co-working spaces will come up on the beach.

news.title: Mumbai: With nowhere to go, residents stay put in unsafe buildings
news.para: Before the monsoon this year, the BMC declared 337 residential buildings in Mumbai dangerous. Civic officials said that out of these buildings, 163 are in the western suburbs, 104 are in the eastern suburbs, wherein 70 buildings are in the island city.

news.title: Delhi civic body starts tendering process for digitising 10,000 properties
news.para: Officials said that the hard copy/original documents of some of these properties are lying in a deplorable state and their digitisation is a must for future reference.

news.title: Greater Noida: No work for 15 years, GNIDA cancels land allotment to Assotech Infrastructure
news.para: Assotech Infrastructure was allotted 18,141 square metres of land in 2006. The builder also took possession of the plot in October 2006 following the execution of a lease deed but never went ahead with the project.

news.title: Kolkata: Online sanction of building plan in 15 days
news.para: Mayor Firhad Hakim on Saturday asked the municipal commissioner Binod Kumar to look into the matter and issue a circular in this regard.

news.title: Cash-starved Ludhiana civic body yet to revise rents on properties
news.para: ​The local bodies department, while approving the annual budget of civic body in the month of May, had asked them to re-negotiate rent agreement with tenants according to new rent control act.

news.title: Lucknow development body seeks expansion of jurisdiction
news.para: The proposal will be first presented in the board meeting of the housing and urban planning department on Monday and then to the government for approval.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC's stop-work order on redevelopment worries Bhendi Bazaar residents
news.para: Construction on the first phase of the work began in 2016 and was completed in 2019, rehabilitating 610 families and 128 businesses in two towers named Al Saadah or prosperity.
